sms_history.message: I just found out that whales have belly buttons.
Wait, what? For real?
Yeah! I mean, it makes sense, they're mammals. But I'd just never thought about it before.
My mind is blown. I'm picturing a giant whale with a little 'innie' belly button.
Right? It's so weirdly humanizing.
What other weird animal facts do you have for me?
A snail can sleep for three years.
Okay, now I'm jealous of a snail.
The world is a weird and wonderful place.
And now I'm going to be thinking about whale belly buttons all day.
That meeting was a black hole of time.
Tell me about it. An hour of my life I'll never get back.
It 100% could have been an email. No, a one-sentence text message.
We spent twenty minutes debating the color of a button on the website.
A button that no one is ever going to click!
My will to live was slowly draining away with every mention of 'brand identity.'
I was just doodling in my notebook, trying to look engaged.
I was playing chess against myself in my head.
We need a secret signal for when a meeting has gone off the rails.
Agreed. How about we both just start barking?
Perfect. No one would question it.
I'm trying to find a good book to read. Any recommendations?
What kind of books do you usually like?
I'm a big fan of fantasy and sci-fi.
Have you read 'Project Hail Mary' by Andy Weir?
No, I've only read 'The Martian' by him.
Oh, you have to read it. It's even better, in my opinion.
Really? That's high praise. What's it about?
It's about an astronaut who wakes up on a spaceship with amnesia, and he's the only one who can save humanity. I don't want to spoil anything else.
Okay, you've sold me. I'm going to order it right now.
You won't regret it! Let me know what you think.
What's the stupidest thing you've ever done for money?
In college, I participated in a paid medical study where I had to eat nothing but potatoes for a week.
No way. Just potatoes?
Boiled, baked, mashed... as long as it was a potato. It was awful.
How much did you get paid for that torture?
$200. It seemed like a fortune at the time.
That's wild. Mine was probably trying to fix my friend's plumbing based on a YouTube video.
How did that go?
I flooded his bathroom. Ended up costing me more than if I had just called a plumber.
We've all been there. Young, dumb, and broke.
I can't decide what to make for dinner.
Same here. I'm tired of all my usual recipes.
What about that creamy tomato pasta we made that one time?
Ooh, that's a great idea! I think I have all the ingredients too.
Do we have heavy cream? I feel like we used it all last week.
Let me check... Nope, you're right, we're out.
Darn. I could run to the store real quick.
Or we could just order takeout. I'm feeling lazy.
Haha, sold. Thai food?
You read my mind. I'll text you the menu.
Hey, can I ask you a question about the 'Dune' book?
Sure, I just finished it last month. What's up?
I'm a little confused about the Bene Gesserit's motivations. What's their ultimate goal?
It's complex, but they're basically playing the long game with politics and genetics to guide humanity.
So they're trying to breed a superbeing, the Kwisatz Haderach?
Exactly. They want to create someone who can see into the future and control it, ensuring humanity's survival.
That makes more sense now. I was getting lost in all the political maneuvering.
It's a lot to take in! The world-building is incredibly dense.
For sure. I'm loving it though. Thanks for clearing that up.
Anytime! Let me know what you think when you finish it.
Do you think plants have feelings?
What? No. They don't have central nervous systems.
I know, but I was just talking to my fern and I swear it perked up.
You were talking to your fern.
Yeah, telling it how nice its leaves are looking. Positive reinforcement.
It probably perked up because the carbon dioxide from your breath is good for it.
You and your science. I think it likes the attention.
Okay, well, don't let me stand in the way of your plant friendships.
I won't. Frank the fern and I are very happy together.
You named it Frank. Of course you did.
I can't decide what to make for dinner.
Same here. I'm tired of all my usual recipes.
What about that creamy tomato pasta we made that one time?
Ooh, that's a great idea! I think I have all the ingredients too.
Do we have heavy cream? I feel like we used it all last week.
Let me check... Nope, you're right, we're out.
Darn. I could run to the store real quick.
Or we could just order takeout. I'm feeling lazy.
Haha, sold. Thai food?
You read my mind. I'll text you the menu.
Remember when we thought frosted tips were the peak of fashion?
Don't remind me. I have photo evidence of me with that haircut.
And the super baggy jeans that were always wet at the bottom from dragging on the ground.
Paired with a puka shell necklace, of course.
It was a dark time for fashion. We were so confident, too.
We thought we were so cool.
What were we thinking?
We weren't. That was the problem. Our brains were just full of dial-up internet noises.
That's probably accurate. I'm going to go burn those old photos now.
Too late. I already have them saved.
Yo, are we still on for D&D this Friday? 🐉
Bet. But we need to talk about your character's alignment.
What about it? Gnorman is a chaotic good gnome. He's a free spirit!
Dude, you tried to pickpocket the king. In front of his royal guards. That's not chaotic good, that's chaotic stupid.
It was for the thrill of it! He was gonna give the gold back... probably.
My Paladin is having an existential crisis because of you. He can't smite his own party member.
😂 Okay fine, I'll tone it down. No more regicide attempts.
Thank you. I'm trying to run a serious campaign here, not a blooper reel.
Lies. You love my shenanigans. Who's bringing snacks?
I'll grab the chips if you bring the soda. And don't forget your dice this time.
No cap, I'll remember. My new set just came in the mail. They're so shiny. ✨
How do I get red wine out of a white shirt?
Oh no! Did you have a spill?
Yes, at dinner last night. It's my favorite shirt too.
Okay, don't panic. Did you put anything on it yet?
No, it's just been sitting there.
First, blot it with a clean cloth. Then, pour some salt or baking soda on the stain to absorb the wine.
Okay, doing that now. Then what?
Let it sit for a bit, then rinse it with cold water from the back of the stain. After that, you can treat it with a stain remover and wash it.
You're a laundry wizard. Thank you!
Haha, I've had my fair share of wine stains. Let me know if it works!
My computer is so slow, I think a sloth could outrun it.
When was the last time you restarted it?
Umm... last week? Maybe?
Dude. You have to restart it every day. That's rule number one.
I know, I just have too many tabs open that I 'need'.
You're a tab hoarder. Close some of them. Your computer's RAM is crying for help.
Fine, fine. I'm restarting it now. I'm sorry, little computer.
Also, check how much storage space you have left. If it's almost full, that'll slow it down too.
Okay, it's back on and it's already so much faster. You're a wizard.
I'm not a wizard, I just listen to the IT department.

I swear, my boss is a vampire. He just sucks the life out of every room he enters.
LMAO. What did he do now?
He scheduled a mandatory meeting for 5 PM on a Friday to 'circle back' on an email thread.
That should be illegal. That's a crime against humanity.
And the whole time he was just talking in circles, a complete fog of corporate jargon.
Let me guess: 'synergize,' 'paradigm shift,' 'low-hanging fruit'?
Bingo. My soul literally tried to leave my body.
You need to get out of there. That place is a prison of mediocrity.
I'm working on it. Polishing up the ol' resume as we speak.
Good. Fly, you fool!  Gandalf
Can I vent for a second?
Always. What's up?
My brother just announced he's getting married... on the same weekend as my birthday.
Ouch. That's rough. Did he know?
I think he just forgot. But still! It feels like he's stealing my thunder.
I get why you'd be upset. That's a pretty big oversight.
Now my whole family is going to be focused on the wedding and my birthday will just be an afterthought.
Have you talked to him about it?
Not yet. I don't want to seem selfish.
You're not being selfish, you're just hurt. Your feelings are valid.
Thanks for saying that. I just needed someone to tell me I wasn't crazy.
I think I'm officially old.
Why? What happened?
I hurt my back sleeping.
Ah, yes. The 'I did absolutely nothing and now I'm in pain' injury. Welcome to the club.
It's so embarrassing! I literally just woke up and couldn't stand up straight.
Did you try putting a heating pad on it?
Yep. I'm currently lying on the floor with a heating pad, questioning all my life choices.
We need to start doing yoga or something. We're too young to be this decrepit.
Agreed. As soon as I can move again, we're signing up for a class.
Sounds good. Feel better, old man.
The cat threw up on the rug again.
Which one? The new one in the living room?
The very same. The expensive one.
Of course. It's like he has a sixth sense for things we value.
I cleaned it up but there's a stain. Can you grab the special carpet cleaner on your way home?
Yeah, no problem. Is he acting okay otherwise?
He's fine. He's currently purring on my lap like a little furry agent of chaos.
Typical. He knows he's too cute to stay mad at.
It's his superpower. That and projectile vomiting.
What a talented boy. I'll be home soon.

I just checked our joint account. Where did $300 go?
Oh, about that... I had to buy the new graphics card.
Are you kidding me? The 'had to'? We agreed to talk about any purchase over $100.
I know, I know, but it was a flash sale and it was the last one in stock!
That's the excuse every single time. It's like you think money just grows on trees.
It was a really good deal! I'll make it up, I swear.
How? By magically finding another 'good deal' on something else we don't need? This is bullshit.
Look, I messed up. I'm sorry. I got caught up in the moment.
I'm just so tired of this. We have a budget for a reason.
I know. I'll return it first thing tomorrow.
You better.

I just had the weirdest dream.
Do tell.
I was in a grocery store, but all the food was replaced with office supplies.
So you were shopping for staplers and paper clips?
Yeah, and I was trying to find ripe avocados but they were just green highlighters.
Your brain is a weird place. What does that even mean?
I think it means I'm stressed about work and I'm also hungry.
Sounds about right. The subconscious is not subtle.
Now I really want some guacamole.
Just make sure you don't use highlighters.
I'm making a playlist. Give me a song that makes you feel nostalgic.
'Mr. Brightside' by The Killers.
A classic. That's a universal high school experience in a song.
It's impossible not to scream the lyrics when it comes on.
Okay, what about a song that makes you want to drive with the windows down?
Easy. 'Golden' by Harry Styles.
Perfect choice. Adding it now.
What's the vibe of this playlist? What are you calling it?
It's called 'Main Character Energy.' For when you need to romanticize your life.
I love it. Send me the link when you're done.

I'm trying to be healthier. Any tips for easy lunches?
Salads are always a good option. You can prep a bunch of ingredients at the start of the week.
I get so bored of salads though.
Then you're not making them right! You need to add lots of different textures and flavors. Nuts, seeds, cheese, a good dressing.
That sounds like a lot of work.
What about quinoa bowls? Or wraps with hummus and veggies?
Wraps could work. That seems manageable.
Yeah, they're super easy and you can switch up the fillings so you don't get bored.
Okay, I'll give that a try this week. Thanks for the ideas!
No problem! Healthy eating doesn't have to be boring.
I'm trying to learn how to play the guitar.
That's so cool! How's it going?
It's... hard. My fingers hurt and I can't seem to make the chords sound right.
That's totally normal at the beginning. You have to build up calluses on your fingertips.
How long does that take?
A few weeks of consistent practice. Don't give up!
Any tips for a beginner?
Start with simple songs that only use a few basic chords. And use a YouTube tutorial, they're super helpful.
Okay, I'll try that. Thanks for the encouragement.
You'll be a rockstar in no time. 🎸
Do you remember your first concert?
Vaguely. I think it was some local band at a fair.
My first real concert was Green Day in 2005.
No way! The 'American Idiot' tour? I'm so jealous.
Yes! It was amazing. My ears were ringing for days afterwards.
That must have been such a great show.
It was life-changing for 15-year-old me. What was the first big concert you went to?
I think it was The Killers, around 2008. They were incredible live.
Oh, I bet they were. Brandon Flowers has so much energy.
He really does. It's fun to think about how much our music taste has changed since then.
I can't believe summer is almost over.
I know. It flew by in the blink of an eye.
I feel like I didn't do enough summery things.
We still have a few weeks! We need to make a bucket list.
Okay, what's on it? Beach trip is a must.
Bonfire with s'mores.
Go to an outdoor concert.
Eat way too much ice cream.
This is a solid list. Let's start this weekend.
Deal. We're going to squeeze every last drop out of this summer.
My flight got delayed by three hours.
No! Are you stuck at the airport?
Yep. And it's packed in here. I can't even find a place to sit.
That's the worst. Did they say why it was delayed?
Something about a mechanical issue with the plane.
Well, I'm glad they caught it on the ground, at least.
True. But now I'm going to miss my connecting flight.
Are they rebooking you?
They said they'll have more information soon. For now, I'm just waiting in a huge line.
Hang in there. Let me know what happens.
I got the job!
NO WAY! The one at the design firm?
YES! They called me this morning with the offer!
AHHHH I'M SO PROUD OF YOU! This is incredible news!
Thank you! I'm so excited I can barely sit still.
We have to celebrate. Dinner and drinks on me this weekend.
You don't have to do that!
I absolutely do. This is a huge deal!
Okay, okay, you win. I can't wait to tell you all about it.
Seriously, congratulations. You earned this.

Psst. We need to organize a leaving gift for Brenda.
Oh yeah, her last day is next Friday. What are we thinking?
I was thinking we could all chip in for a nice gift card to that spa she likes.
Good call. How much should we ask people for? $20?
Yeah, that seems fair. I can send out a discreet email to the team.
Okay, and I'll get one of those giant cards that everyone can sign.
Perfect. Should we get a cake too?
Duh. Is that even a question? I'll order one from the good bakery.
This is coming together nicely. Teamwork makes the dream work.
For sure. It'll be a nice send-off. Brenda deserves it.
I'm officially on the Wordle struggle bus today.
Oh no! How many guesses do you have left?
I'm on my last guess. I have _OUND and I can't figure it out.
Is it FOUND?
Nope, already tried that. And ROUND, and SOUND.
What about MOUND? Or POUND?
Tried those too! This is impossible.
Okay, think of weirder letters. HOUND? WOUND?
WOUND! Let me try... YES! That was it!
Phew! Streak saved. That was a close one.
You're my hero. I was about to throw my phone.
Remember when we thought frosted tips were the peak of fashion?
Don't remind me. I have photo evidence of me with that haircut.

Paired with a puka shell necklace, of course.

Too late. I already have them saved.
What are you doing for Thanksgiving this year?
I think I'm just going to stay here. Flying home is so expensive.
You should come to my family's dinner!
Are you sure? I don't want to impose.
Don't be silly! We'd love to have you. My mom always makes way too much food.
That's so nice of you to offer. I might take you up on that.
Please do! It will be fun. And my grandma makes the best pie.
Okay, you've convinced me. What can I bring?
Just bring yourself! I'm so glad you're coming.
Me too. Thank you so much.
I can't believe we've known each other for 10 years.
I know, right? It feels like just yesterday we were freshmen in college.
Remember trying to navigate the campus on the first day? We were so lost.
And we both ended up in the wrong lecture hall!
That's how we met! In that boring philosophy class we weren't even enrolled in.
It's crazy how much has changed since then.
And how much hasn't. We're still just as ridiculous.
Hey, speak for yourself! But yeah, you're right.
To ten years of friendship! 🍻
And hopefully many more to come.

Okay, it's in your inbox.
Reading it now... Hmm. It's good, but this one sentence sounds a little passive-aggressive.
Which one?
'As per my last email, the data is attached.' It sounds a little snarky.
Well, I AM being snarky. This is the third time he's asked for it.
I know, but you can't let him know that. Try something like, 'Just re-attaching the data here for your convenience!'
Ugh. The corporate dance. You're right, that's better.
Kill 'em with kindness. And excessive exclamation points.
Thanks. You just saved me from a trip to HR. 😂
We need to figure out a gift for Sarah's baby shower.
I was just thinking about that. Did she have a registry?
Yeah, she sent me the link. But all the big stuff is already bought.
What's left on it?
Mostly small things, like diapers, wipes, and some clothes.
We could put together a big gift basket with all of that stuff.
That's a cute idea! And we could add in some things that aren't on the registry, like books or a nice blanket.
Perfect. Let's go shopping for it this weekend.
Sounds like a plan. I'll make a list.
Great. She's going to love it.

Do you ever feel like you're just... floating? Not really anchored to anything?
All the time. Like I'm just going through the motions waiting for my life to actually start.
Exactly! I have a good job, good friends... but it feels hollow sometimes.
I get that. It's like I'm a ship without a rudder, just being pushed around by the current.
That's a perfect way to put it. I keep thinking I should make a big change, but I don't even know what that would be.
Maybe it's not about a big change. Maybe it's about finding small things that feel real.
Like what?
I don't know... a hobby? Volunteering? Something that's just for you, not for your career or anyone else.
That's... actually really good advice. It feels less daunting than 'find your purpose.'
We're all just figuring it out. One day at a time.
What's the name of that song that goes 'doo-doo-dah-dah-dee-dah'?
You're going to have to be way more specific than that.
It's like an indie pop song, kind of upbeat. A female singer.
Is it new? Old?
I think from the 2010s? It was in a commercial recently.
Okay, I might have an idea. Is it 'Walking on a Dream' by Empire of the Sun?
No, that's not it. The singer has a higher voice.
Hmm... '1234' by Feist?
Let me look it up... YES! That's it! You're a genius.
Haha, I have my moments. Glad I could solve the mystery.
Did you get my email about the team meeting on Friday?
Yes, I saw it. Do we really need another meeting?
I think so. We need to get aligned on the Q4 goals.
Couldn't this have been an email? My week is already so packed.
I considered that, but there are a few points I think we need to discuss in real time.
Fine. But can we try to keep it to 30 minutes?
That's the plan. I'll send out a clear agenda tomorrow to keep us on track.
Okay, I appreciate that.
No problem. I don't want to waste anyone's time.
Thanks. See you then.
I'm trying to cut back on coffee. This is my first day.
How's that going for you?
I have a headache that could shatter glass and I've snapped at three different coworkers.
Sounds about right. The caffeine withdrawal is no joke.
Why am I doing this to myself? Coffee is my lifeblood.
Maybe just cut back instead of quitting cold turkey? Like, one cup instead of four.
That's a much more reasonable idea. Quitting is for quitters.
There you go. Baby steps.
I'm going to go make a cup right now. Thank you for talking me off that ledge.
Anytime. I didn't want to have to deal with you being a monster all week.
This weather is giving me whiplash.
I know. It was sunny this morning and now it's hailing.
I wore shorts today. I have so many regrets.
You have to dress in layers. It's the only way to survive.
I feel like Mother Nature is just messing with us at this point.
She's keeping us on our toes.
My car is getting dented by these giant hailstones.
Mine too. At least we'll match.
This is fine. Everything is fine. 🔥
Just another beautiful day in paradise.
That meeting was a black hole of time.
Tell me about it. An hour of my life I'll never get back.
